        <name>UartNs550HelloWorldExample</name>
        <param>
          <type>UINTPTR</type>
          <declname>BaseAddress</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>This function sends Hello World with the UART 16450/550 device and driver as a design example. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The purpose of this function is to illustrate how to use the <ref refid="struct_x_uart_ns550" kindref="compound">XUartNs550</ref> driver.</para><para>This function polls the UART and does not require the use of interrupts.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>BaseAddress</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>contains the base address of the device</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_FAILURE if the UART driver could not be initialized successfully.</para></listitem><listitem><para>A non-negative number indicating the number of characters sent.</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>In XSCT/classic flow, DeviceId is used to look up the device configuration. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
